.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}, {"id": 1118559391, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMTE4NTU5Mzkx", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-doctests", "name": "A-doctests", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Documentation tests, run by rustdoc"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2019-01-03T21:42:16Z", "updated_at": "2019-01-05T20:22:53Z", "closed_at": "2019-01-05T20:22:53Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```rust\r\n//! ```\r\n//! #![crate_name = \"asdf\"]\r\n//!\r\n//! println!(\"yo\");\r\n//! ```\r\n```\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ rustdoc +nightly u.rs --test\r\n\r\nrunning 1 test\r\ntest u.rs -  (line 1) ... FAILED\r\n\r\nfailures:\r\n\r\n---- u.rs -  (line 1) stdout ----\r\nthread 'u.rs -  (line 1)' panicked at 'couldn't run the test: No such file or directory (os error 2)', src/librustdoc/test.rs:343:19\r\nnote: Run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace.\r\n\r\n\r\nfailures:\r\n    u.rs -  (line 1)\r\n\r\ntest result: FAILED. 0 passed; 1 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out\r\n```\r\n\r\nBased on investigation in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-by-example/issues/1137#issuecomment-451136118, rustdoc hardcodes the name of the doctest executable to run, but manually setting a `#![crate_name]` attribute changes the name of this executable. This causes the above error, because rustdoc is trying to run the wrong executable.", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followers", "following_url": "https://api.git